<TITLE> M Morshed's son gets 10 years for graft </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 20 (bdnews24.com) A Dhaka court Wednesday sentenced M Faisal Morshed Khan, son of former foreign minister M Morshed Khan, to a total of 10 years in prison on charges of amassing wealth beyond known sources of income. Judge AKM Arifur Rahman, of Special Court-10 set up in the Sangsad Bhaban premises, also fined Faisal Tk 10 lakh or another year's jail term in case of failure to pay. The court ordered the state to confiscate property worth Tk 1.66 crore acquired illegally by the convict. Faisal's sentence comprised two termseight years for amassing illegal wealth and another two for concealing wealth related information from the Anticorruption Commission. The two terms, to be effective from the day of the fugitive Faisal's arrest or surrender, will be served consecutively. The ACC filed the case against Faisal and wife Cezanne Khan on Dec 1, 2007, with Gulshan police. Trial of the case against Cezanne being stayed by the higher court is currently suspended. Faisal already faces a seven year sentence in a separate graft case. bdnews24.
